(1) Newtown Road, west from the S.E. corner of 47th Street, showing in their order, prominently NOS. 47-08, 46-16, 46-02, and 45-18. These houses are a few that remain in the Middleton settlement, started about 1800. This settlement was located on Newtown Ave., between Grand Ave. and Broadway.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing also the north side of the street.

April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing a close-up of the S.W. corner.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

47-01 Newtown Road, at the N.E. corner of 47th Street, showing an old house, typical of late nineteenth century construction. In rear of it, on 48th Street, is an old farmhouse. Later views show also the rear of the new William Cullen Bryant High School. 47th Street is in the foreground. The house was owned by J. Murphy in 1873.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: October 31, 1936
Views 2,3: September 5, 1940
